'''Kelvin Spencer Pires''' ({{IPA|pt|ˈkɛl.vin ˈspɛ̃.sɛɾ ˈpi.ɾɨʃ|lang}}; born 5 June 2000) is a Cape Verdean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|centre back]] for [[Veikkausliiga]] club [[Seinäjoen Jalkapallokerho|SJK]] and the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Club career==
Pires made his [[Slovak Super Liga|Fortuna Liga]] debut for [[AS Trenčín]] against [[FC Spartak Trnava]] on 6 March 2021.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/03/06/slovakia/super-liga/fk-as-trencin/fc-spartak-trnava/3311923/ TRENČÍN VS. SPARTAK TRNAVA 2 - 0] 06.03.2021, soccerway.com</ref>

On 6 February 2024, Pires was loaned out to Finnish [[Veikkausliiga]] club [[Seinäjoen Jalkapallokerho|SJK Seinäjoki]] for the [[2024 Veikkausliiga|2024]] season.<ref>[https://sjk.fi/uutiset/tervetuloa-kelvin-pires/ Tervetuloa Kelvin Pires!], sjk.fi, 6 February 2024</ref>

On 14 November 2024, Pires signed a permanent contract with SJK, on a two-year deal with a two-year option, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>[https://sjk.fi/uutiset/sjk-hankki-kelvin-piresin-pysyvasti-riveihinsa/ SJK hankki Kelvin Piresin pysyvästi riveihinsä], sjk.fi, 14 November 2024</ref>

==International career==
Pires made his debut with the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] [[Estádio Municipal Adérito Sena|home]] fixture with [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] on 4 September 2021. He was featured in the starting-XI and completed the entirety of the match. Cape Verde lost 1–2.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Cape Verde Islands vs. Nigeria - 7 September 2021 - Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/09/07/africa/wc-qualifying-africa/cape-verde-islands/nigeria/3500850/|access-date=2021-09-07|website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref>

